12/11/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Macedonia, Bosnia and Herzegovina and Serbia-Montenegro are the countries with the highest political risk in Europe, according to a report, RiskMap 2004, released Tuesday (11 November).
The international business risk consultants, Control Risks Group, surveyed 130 countries for more than 5,300 investors.
Also Tuesday, experts attending a roundtable in Skopje agreed that Macedonia needs a law on crisis management, one that clearly defines the role of the Macedonian Army in emergency situations.
A draft bill is due to be submitted to the government.
(Dnevnik, BTA - 12/11/03;
Control Risks Group Web site, MIA - 11/11/03)
